  		<div><h3>Comments</h3></div>
  		<div>
  			<div id="item-1413"><p>I use a rubber (or silicone) spatula to sort of gently scramble the eggs, or sort of fold them over on themselves to let the runny part run over the cooked part and get cooked, but not too cooked if you like your omelets soft, like I do. Then I do use the spatula to nudge them up toward the edge of the pan, and then tip the pan over so they fall out in a crescent shape onto your plate. You shouldn&#8217;t really need to cover the pan to melt the cheese, because the cheese should be folded into the center of the omelet and the heat from the egg should be enough to do it. Especially since you&#8217;re not using that much cheese; you don&#8217;t want to overwhelm the egg.</p>
<p>Mommy</p></div>
